spanGrp.span: Ji sũã'-nẽ yís të-ra je rö jeñẽ yë böi-nẽ
porke jirö nẽ í kie rö
Someone was coming in a car
when a fucking duck appeared, walking, on the road.
Jeska tõglö chi dasõ-tö ñala wa shkö-gẽ-nẽ
The man was carrying his load wrapped up like a ball;
Pekaga deli í shkö wa paböt-lë-wã se të í sũẽ (_) rö bola kepibi
Then there were other things that looked like cows.
Jekepanẽ mãga jirö tsõ-nẽ í wa mẽi yu-lë-nẽ rö baga kepinẽ
The fucking ball ended up there and they started to play with it.
Je chi nẽ (m) je je de-mĩ-sãu-nẽ tögapanẽ je-wa tsõ-nẽ jinõ je wa
Who says they can play like that?
¿Yurö të í she-nã je-wa rö jinõ ta je-wa nã
Then the fucking little pigs were laughing and playing too.
Jeskanẽ mãga kuchi yabla chi jalali nẽ jiñõ-gẽ-nẽ jinõ-gẽ ĩã nẽ
And there appeared a fucking dog;
Jeska mãga chichi chi tsõ nãteĩã'nẽ
Í chi të bola ñã bestse-gẽ (_) ñã ra
And as they were playing something broke;
Jekepa mãĩ í chi jinõ-gẽ-mĩ-wã jinõ-gẽ-mĩ-wã ska nẽ je kaũte pe jelë kwã'-wã e-gla kwã'-wã
the dog told another one to come in through a small hole, so he could open the door;
jekepa chichi të e-gla pakká-nẽ köwãu-nẽ uekiyo jãrga nã jukö youmĩ-nẽ ĩã
Jekea í wakwa chi ñã bö'gate-nẽ jeska nẽ
He did as told, walked to the little pigs
Je yuwá-ite kau-mĩ-nẽ kwãwã nẽ kuchi yabla chi jalali ska nẽ
and there the assholes did it;
jeska ra jie-wa (m) chi të yuá-nẽ
the fucking cows stood up uff! and climbed on top of one another and got to where the fucking little pigs were playing;
Jekepa baga-wa chi ñã ga-ká-nẽ u ñã jiá-ka-nẽ teki inga e-gla teki inga e-gla teki inga nẽ Degãu-lo-nẽ mãĩ kuchi yabla chi jalali jinõ ska nẽ
So, three little pigs also climbed on top of one another.
jekepa kuchi yabla (_) tres ñã jalá-ka-nẽ jieb nẽ teki kicha inga (m) teki kicha inga
they were playing under a tree and broke a window with the ball;
jeska í tsõ-nẽ kal diginã jinõ-nẽ Kepa jele bidrio kwã'-wã-nẽ-ite je bola wa jinõ-gẽ-wã të bidrio kwã'-wa
so, the assholes hid behind a tree;
kepa í chi ñã blá-ka-wã kal digi/ kal teki mẽ nẽ
two of them were on a tree branch;
Jeska bo-l-wa chi kete-nẽ kaljula jãrga nẽ
the dog took it inside the house.
Chichi të í pakká-wã-nẽ jũ jãrga nẽ
They were playing, but who says that cows play with balls? Who says that a pig or a dog can kick a ball?
Je í chi të jinõ tel-nẽ í të bola tie-gẽ ¿yurö keglö í she baga të bola tie ta kuchi të (m) bola tie ta chichi të bola tie ta
they lifted the ball in the air and the dogs and the pigs rose high in the air trying to catch the ball.
Í kau-mĩ-nẽ (hm) (hm) bola butsá-ka-ite siwã inga (_) chichi í rö kuchi-wa (_) ñã butsá-ka siwã inga komĩ' (_) shö-glö-nã jie-wa wã bola (_) gugö-glö-wã
the duck was flying the ball went through its beak;
Jekepa mãga jeska tõglö jurra-mĩ-nẽ je tiá bola të plaja kau-mĩ ñawã jãrga
it fell down with its belly full because of the ball [it had swallowed].
